question_title: Will OpenAI release a model named 'GPT-6' for general public availability before May 1, 2026?
summary: OpenAI releasing a model named "GPT-6" for general public availability before May 1, 2026 is very unlikely. As of February 2026, OpenAI is still actively iterating on the GPT-5.x series (GPT-5.3-Codex was just released on Feb 5, 2026). No official GPT-6 release date has been announced - only vague "sometime in 2026" guidance. Multiple credible sources place the likely release window at mid-to-late 2026 or even early 2027 for general availability. The Manifold market for "GPT-6 before June 1, 2026" (one month LATER than this question) trades at only ~17%. With only ~3 months until the deadline and no announcement, preview, or concrete timeline, this is extremely unlikely.

factors.description: OpenAI still actively releasing GPT-5.x series (5.3-Codex released Feb 5, 2026), indicating GPT-6 is not imminent
No official GPT-6 release date announced; only vague 'sometime in 2026' guidance from OpenAI
Manifold market for 'GPT-6 before June 1, 2026' at only 16.6% - May 1 deadline is one month earlier
Multiple sources project private previews mid-2026 and public release later 2026 or early 2027
Sam Altman said GPT-5→6 gap would be shorter than GPT-4→5 (2.5 years), and OpenAI has accelerated release cadence
Only ~3 months until May 1 deadline - even if announced soon, general public availability requires additional rollout time
